using Plots, Distributions, StatsBase, Random

\[ K(x) = \begin{cases} 1, & \textrm{if $x \in [-0.5, 0.5]$}, \\ 0, & \textrm{otherwise.} \end{cases} \]

p1 = plot(x -> -0.5 <= x <= 0.5
     , -1, 1
     , legend = false
     , xlabel = "x"
     , ylabel = "K(x)"
     , title = "Rectangular kernel");

\[ K(x) = \max\{1 - |x|, 0\}. \]

p2 = plot(x -> max(1 - abs(x), 0)
     , -1.5, 1.5
     , legend = false
     , xlabel = "x"
     , ylabel = "K(x)"
     , title = "Triangular kernel");

\[ K(x) = \varphi(x). \]

p3 = plot(x -> pdf(Normal(), x)
     , -4, 4
     , legend = false
     , xlabel = "x"
     , ylabel = "K(x)"
     , title = "Gaussian kernel");

\[ K(x) = \frac{3}{4}\max\{1 - x^2, 0\}. \]

p4 = plot(x -> 3/4*max(1 - x^2, 0)
     , -1.5, 1.5
     , legend = false
     , xlabel = "x"
     , ylabel = "K(x)"
     , title = "Epanechnikov kernel");
plot(p1, p2, p3, p4, layout = (2, 2), legend = false)
Random.seed!(2023-09-05);
epsilon = 0.2;
main_distribution = Beta(7, 2);
secondary_distribution = Beta(1, 10);
total_n = 412;
pure_n = rand(Binomial(total_n, 1 - epsilon), 1)[1];
data = [rand(main_distribution, pure_n); rand(secondary_distribution, total_n - pure_n)];
histogram(data, normalize = :pdf
          , legend = false
          , color = "lightgrey")
function mixture_pdf(x)
  return (1 - epsilon) * pdf(main_distribution, x) + epsilon * pdf(secondary_distribution, x)
end;
function gaussian_kde(x, data, h)
  norm_dist = Normal()
  scaled_data = (x .- data) ./ h
  kde = 1/h * mean(pdf.(norm_dist, scaled_data))
  return kde
end;
function triangular_kde(x, data, h)
  scaled_data = (x .- data) ./ h
  kde = 1/h * mean(max.(1 .- abs.(scaled_data), 0))
  return kde
end;
function rectangular_kde(x, data, h)
  scaled_data = (x .- data) ./ h
  kde = 1/h * mean(-0.5 .<= scaled_data .<= 0.5)
  return kde
end;
function epanechnikov_kde(x, data, h)
  scaled_data = (x .- data) ./ h
  kde = 3/(4h) * mean(max.(1 .- scaled_data.^2, 0))
  return kde
end;
plot(x -> mixture_pdf(x)
     , -0.2, 1.2
     , linewidth = 3
     , label = "actual pdf"
     , main = "Triangular kernel")
plot!(x -> triangular_kde(x, data, 1/10)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.1)")
plot!(x -> triangular_kde(x, data, 1/5)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.2)")
plot!(x -> triangular_kde(x, data, 1/20)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.05)")
plot(x -> mixture_pdf(x)
     , -0.2, 1.2
     , linewidth = 3
     , label = "actual pdf"
     , main = "Rectangular kernel")
plot!(x -> rectangular_kde(x, data, 1/10)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.1)")
plot!(x -> rectangular_kde(x, data, 1/5)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.2)")
plot!(x -> rectangular_kde(x, data, 1/20)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.05)")
plot(x -> mixture_pdf(x)
     , -0.2, 1.2
     , linewidth = 3
     , label = "actual pdf"
     , main = "Epanechnikov kernel")
plot!(x -> epanechnikov_kde(x, data, 1/10)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.1)")
plot!(x -> epanechnikov_kde(x, data, 1/5)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.2)")
plot!(x -> epanechnikov_kde(x, data, 1/20)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.05)")
plot(x -> mixture_pdf(x)
     , -0.2, 1.2
     , linewidth = 3
     , label = "actual pdf"
     , main = "Gaussian kernel")
plot!(x -> gaussian_kde(x, data, 1/10)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.1)")
plot!(x -> gaussian_kde(x, data, 1/5)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.2)")
plot!(x -> gaussian_kde(x, data, 1/20)
      , linewidth = 3
      , label = "estimated pdf (bandwidth 0.05)")
p = plot(x -> gaussian_kde(x, data, 1/10)
         , -0.2, 1.2)
for i in 1:length(data)
  plot!(p
        , x -> 1/10 * gaussian_kde(x, data[i], 1/10)
        , legend = false
        , color = "turquoise")
end
display(p)
function empirical_cdf(x, data)
  return mean(data .<= x)
end

function massart(alpha, n)
  return (log(2/alpha)/(2n))^(1/2)
end

plot(x -> empirical_cdf(x, data)
     , -0.2, 1.2)
plot!(x -> min(empirical_cdf(x, data) + massart(0.05, length(data)), 1))
plot!(x -> max(empirical_cdf(x, data) - massart(0.05, length(data)), 0))
